Firewall Manager automatically distributes tags from the primary group
to the security groups created by this policy. To use security group
tag distribution, you must also set C<revertManualSecurityGroupChanges>
to C<true>, otherwise Firewall Manager won't be able to create the
policy. When you enable C<revertManualSecurityGroupChanges>, Firewall
Manager identifies and reports when the security groups created by this
policy become non-compliant.

Firewall Manager won't distribute system tags added by Amazon Web
Services services into the replica security groups. System tags begin
with the C<aws:> prefix.

